this is a review of the new ASAP mob
mixtape Lords never worry ASAP mob is a
new hip-hop outfit from New York City
fronted by MC main brain hip-hop
personality ASAP rocky who released a
pretty big mixtape last year Live Love
ASAP that I reviewed personally and and
gave a very positive review to and for
good reason it was really fresh sounding
mixtape you know the dude just came out
with a hybrid of pretty interesting
styles put together in a way that just
sounded like a great idea
the songs on this mixtape reference
everything from spacious little B style
cloud rap to bone thugs-n-harmony and
there was something very southern about
a lot of the beats on this thing too
with the chopped and screwed vocal
samples and and instrumentals I also
kind of like ASAP Rocky's very
simplistic minimal flow over these very
spacious shoegaze II kind of ethereal
instrumentals the guy has a full-length
album his debut album coming out later
this year but in the meantime to kind of
hold fans over he has released this new
mixtape with his ASAP outfit and I got
to say to be completely honest this
thing was an extreme disappointment
there is not an angle at which you can
look at this tape that would make it
look pretty first let's kind of take on
this thing instrumentally because let's
be honest the instrumentals were a huge
huge part in making live love ASAP good

one clams casino B isn't even really one

they are just riding some really
cut-rate
